FROM - Specifies the base image to be used for the build.

MAINTAINER - Specifies the author or maintainer of the image.

RUN - Executes a command within the container.

CMD - Specifies the default command to be executed when the container starts.

ENTRYPOINT - Specifies the command that will be run when the container starts.

ENV - Sets an environment variable within the container.

EXPOSE - Exposes a port to the host machine.

ADD - Copies files from the host machine to the container.

COPY - Copies files from the host machine to the container.

WORKDIR - Sets the working directory for the container.

USER - Sets the user that will run the container.

VOLUME - Creates a volume in the container.

ARG - Defines a build-time argument.

